# CrossQL — Repository Review & Analysis (Through Phase 9)

## Project Overview

CrossQL is a **desktop ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) application** built with:

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Desktop shell | **Tauri 2** |
| Frontend | **Svelte 5** (Runes) + **Tailwind CSS** |
| Canvas | **Svelte Flow** (`@xyflow/svelte`) |
| Data engine | **Polars** (Rust LazyFrame) |
| Connectors | `sqlx` (Postgres, MySQL), [mongodb](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#387-432), `cdrs-tokio` (Cassandra) |

Users visually build pipelines on a drag-and-drop canvas connecting sources → transforms → Parquet output.

---

## Architecture Summary

```
src/                          (Svelte frontend)
├── routes/+page.svelte       (938 lines — main app page, ALL app logic)
├── lib/types.ts              (TypeScript interfaces for pipeline JSON)
├── lib/components/
│   ├── PipelineCanvas.svelte (Svelte Flow wrapper)
│   ├── TypeBadge.svelte      (Column type badge component)
│   └── nodes/                (12 node components)
│       ├── PostgresSourceNode, MySQLSourceNode, MongoSourceNode, CassandraSourceNode
│       ├── SchemaMapNode, JoinNode
│       ├── FilterNode, SelectNode, RenameNode, CastNode, DerivedColumnNode
│       └── OutputNode

src-tauri/src/                (Rust backend)
├── lib.rs                    (Tauri app builder, command registration)
├── main.rs                   (Entry point)
├── commands.rs               (508 lines — 17 Tauri commands)
├── run_manager.rs            (79 lines — run lifecycle + cancellation)
├── connectors/
│   ├── postgres.rs, mysql.rs, mongodb.rs, cassandra.rs
├── engine/
│   ├── pipeline.rs           (635 lines — DAG execution engine)
│   ├── schema.rs             (130 lines — schema map + null handling)
│   └── transform.rs          (224 lines — filter, select, rename, cast, derived)
└── writer/
    └── parquet.rs            (Parquet writer via Polars)
```

