## Phase 9 Review — Pipeline Execution UX

Phase 9 focuses on making pipeline execution responsive and informative. Here's how each requirement was met:

### ✅ Tauri [emit](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#112-117) events per pipeline stage

[commands.rs](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#L102-L116) — [PipelineEvent](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#103-111) struct with `run_id`, `kind`, `node_id`, `state`, `message`, and [result](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/run_manager.rs#23-28) fields. Events emitted via [emit_pipeline_event()](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#112-117) which calls `app.emit("pipeline_event", evt)`.

Event kinds: `run_started`, `node_state`, `run_finished`, `run_cancelled`, `run_error`.

### ✅ Per-node status ring: idle → running → done → error

[commands.rs](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#L144-L222) — On run start, all nodes set to `"running"`. On success, all transition to `"done"`. On error/cancel, all transition to `"error"` or `"idle"`. Frontend listens via `listen<PipelineEvent>('pipeline_event', ...)` and updates `run_state` on each node's data.

### ✅ Execution log panel

[+page.svelte](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src/routes/+page.svelte#L805-L822) — Scrollable log panel in the sidebar. `appendLog()` adds timestamped entries (capped at 300). Shows `toLocaleTimeString()` + message for each event.

### ✅ Cancel running pipeline

[run_manager.rs](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/run_manager.rs) — [RunManager](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/run_manager.rs#40-43) + [RunEntry](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/run_manager.rs#8-13) using `tokio_util::CancellationToken`. [start_pipeline_run](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#118-228) spawns a Tokio task, selects between `cancel.cancelled()` and the actual pipeline future. Frontend calls [cancel_pipeline_run](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#237-249) → triggers cancellation token.

### ✅ Estimated row count between nodes

[pipeline.rs](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/engine/pipeline.rs#L164-L181) — [compute_row_count()](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/engine/pipeline.rs#164-182) computes row counts from cached LazyFrames. [NodeStats](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/engine/pipeline.rs#86-92) with `rows_left`, `rows_right`, `rows_out` generated for each node. Stats applied via `applyNodeStats()` on the frontend.

---

## Strengths

| Area | Details |
|---|---|
| **Architecture** | Clean separation: connectors / engine / writer. Pipeline JSON as source of truth. All processing in Rust. |
| **DAG Engine** | Recursive [node_to_lazyframe()](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/engine/pipeline.rs#211-455) with cycle detection (`visiting` set), result caching (`cache` map), and proper error propagation. |
| **Type System** | Canonical type mapping (PostgreSQL/MySQL/MongoDB/Cassandra → Polars types) with null handling modes (`keep`, `drop_row`, `fill_default`, `error`). |
| **Run Management** | Async pipeline execution with `CancellationToken`, `Notify`-based result waiting, and proper cleanup via [finish_run()](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/run_manager.rs#74-78). |
| **Transform Coverage** | All 5 transform ops (filter, select, rename, cast, derived) implemented as clean Polars LazyFrame expressions. |

---

## Issues & Recommendations

### 🔴 Critical

| # | Issue | Location | Recommendation |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | **[+page.svelte](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src/routes/+page.svelte) is a 938-line monolith** | [+page.svelte](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src/routes/+page.svelte) | Extract into dedicated stores/composables: `pipelineStore.ts`, `schemaPreview.ts`, `executionState.ts`. Move sidebar, config panel, and log panel into separate components. |
| 2 | **Duplicate `run_*_to_parquet` commands** | [commands.rs](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#L259-L492) | These 4 nearly-identical functions (Postgres/MySQL/MongoDB/Cassandra) are dead code — [start_pipeline_run](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#118-228) and [run_pipeline](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#97-101) already use [PipelineEngine](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/engine/pipeline.rs#456-457) which handles all connectors. Remove them. |
| 3 | **[run_mysql_to_parquet](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#305-350) uses [PostgresConfig](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#22-30)** | [commands.rs L306-307](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#L306-L307) | Parameter type is [PostgresConfig](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#22-30) instead of a MySQL-specific type. Type mismatch if these commands were ever used. |
| 4 | **All nodes set to same state simultaneously** | [commands.rs L144-156](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs#L144-L156) | All nodes are marked `running` at the start and `done` at the end, rather than per-node as each completes. True per-node progress would require the pipeline engine to emit events during traversal. |

### 🟡 Important

| # | Issue | Location | Recommendation |
|---|---|---|---|
| 5 | **[RunManager](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/run_manager.rs#40-43) leaks entries on crash** | [run_manager.rs](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/run_manager.rs) | If the spawned task panics, [finish_run()](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/run_manager.rs#74-78) is never called. Add a cleanup mechanism or use `Drop`. |
| 6 | **No `tauri-plugin-dialog`** | [Cargo.toml](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/Cargo.toml) | [package.json](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/package.json) includes `@tauri-apps/plugin-dialog` but [Cargo.toml](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/Cargo.toml) doesn't register the plugin. Phase 10 will need this for file save/open dialogs. |
| 7 | **[node_to_lazyframe](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/engine/pipeline.rs#211-455) recursive future is `Send`** | [pipeline.rs L211-218](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/engine/pipeline.rs#L211-L218) | The recursive async approach with `Pin<Box<dyn Future + Send>>` works but is fragile. Consider converting to an iterative topological sort for better maintainability. |
| 8 | **Duplicate [parse_dtype](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/engine/schema.rs#18-28) function** | [schema.rs](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/engine/schema.rs) and [transform.rs](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/engine/transform.rs) | Both define identical [parse_dtype()](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/engine/schema.rs#18-28). Extract to a shared `types.rs` utility. |
| 9 | **`$effect` triggers on every reactive dependency change** | [+page.svelte L422-424](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src/routes/+page.svelte#L422-L424) | `$effect(() => { void loadSchema(); })` re-triggers on every `nodes`/[edges](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/engine/pipeline.rs#183-186) mutation (since `loadSchema` reads them), causing excessive DB calls. Add debouncing or explicit triggers. |
| 10 | **Hardcoded default credentials** | [+page.svelte L211-218](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src/routes/+page.svelte#L211-L218) | Default node configs include `password: 'postgres'` etc. Phase 12 plans a connection manager, but credentials should never be pre-filled with real values. |

### 🟢 Minor / Polish

| # | Issue | Recommendation |
|---|---|---|
| 11 | **`runId` parameter naming** | [commands.rs](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src-tauri/src/commands.rs) uses `runId` (camelCase) instead of `run_id` (Rust convention). Align naming. |
| 12 | **Empty [README.md](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/README.md)** | Currently just `# CrossQL`. Add project description, setup instructions, phase status. |
| 13 | **No `.editorconfig` / Prettier / rustfmt config** | Add formatting configuration for consistency. |
| 14 | **TypeScript types not used on frontend state** | [+page.svelte](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src/routes/+page.svelte) uses `any[]` for nodes/edges instead of the defined [Pipeline](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src/lib/types.ts#1-8)/[PipelineNode](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src/lib/types.ts#23-29)/[PipelineEdge](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src/lib/types.ts#30-35) types from [types.ts](file:///Users/adev/playground/CrossQL/src/lib/types.ts). |

